WEBVTT

00:00:00.960 --> 00:00:05.759
time we discussed the sequence to

00:00:03.040 --> 00:00:10.080
sequence or seek to seek architecture

00:00:05.759 --> 00:00:13.360
where an encoder that is an RNN takes in

00:00:10.080 --> 00:00:18.080
a sequence let's say a sentence and

00:00:13.360 --> 00:00:23.119
compresses it to a fixed context vector

00:00:18.080 --> 00:00:25.840
and a decoder RNN decodes this vector to

00:00:23.119 --> 00:00:28.000
a translation. We discussed several

00:00:25.840 --> 00:00:29.519
challenges that we had in this

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.399
architecture.

00:00:29.519 --> 00:00:35.200
For example, we should wait for H2 to be

00:00:32.399 --> 00:00:37.280
computed to be able to obtain H3. So

00:00:35.200 --> 00:00:40.239
this means that we cannot really

00:00:37.280 --> 00:00:43.120
parallelize this computation and we

00:00:40.239 --> 00:00:46.399
cannot leverage the full potential of

00:00:43.120 --> 00:00:49.200
our computational power uh in our GPU

00:00:46.399 --> 00:00:52.000
and TPUs. Uh the other issue is of

00:00:49.200 --> 00:00:54.719
course the old issue of uh gradient

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.960
vanishing and explosion because of the

00:00:54.719 --> 00:00:59.760
fact that we are compressing everything

00:00:56.960 --> 00:01:02.559
in this vector and we take it with us.

00:00:59.760 --> 00:01:04.320
We try to take care of this with LSTM

00:01:02.559 --> 00:01:07.760
and gating

00:01:04.320 --> 00:01:10.560
and uh we manage to do a pretty good job

00:01:07.760 --> 00:01:13.760
for short sentences but of course when

00:01:10.560 --> 00:01:16.080
we have longer sentences the issue will

00:01:13.760 --> 00:01:19.040
still be there. So this gradient

00:01:16.080 --> 00:01:21.200
vanishing or explosion, we still have to

00:01:19.040 --> 00:01:23.600
deal with this if we want to go for a

00:01:21.200 --> 00:01:27.920
longer sentence translation for

00:01:23.600 --> 00:01:30.320
instance. But the main problem here is

00:01:27.920 --> 00:01:34.479
really this fixed bottleneck that we

00:01:30.320 --> 00:01:38.000
have and we want to continue from there.

00:01:34.479 --> 00:01:41.439
So here we will focus on this problem

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:44.159
first. Okay. So to make this uh fixed

00:01:41.439 --> 00:01:46.479
